01/03/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- An earthquake measuring 5.9 on the Richter Scale shook southern Greece early Monday (1 March). 
The Thessaloniki Seismological Institute said the epicentre was near the town of Kalamata, 280km southwest of Athens. 
According to the local police, many people spent the night in the streets, but there were no casualties or major damage to property. 
(AP - 01/03/04)
